positive.review:
This game was gifted to me on my birthday. Thank you, brother!

I cannot put it into words to express my amazement towards this game. Kudos to the developers for creating such a unique game play. The story starts simple: you are the nephew of a famous man who will inherit the estate and everything inside it if... If you can find the 46th room. The estate has only 45 rooms in total. Somewhere in the house must be the 46th room. Your mission for the entire week is to find that room. If you fail, the inheritance goes to someone else. If you succeed, you will become the sole heir of the Sinclair family. 

However, it's not as simple as it sounds. You must draft rooms in such a way so as to get to the Antechamber. Each time you get towards a door, you think of a way to craft the estate rooms so as not to get stuck, dead ended or going around in circles. There are gemstones, keys and fruits for stamina. Each day you have a default 50 steps. Each time you enter a room, you will lose a move. Oh my God... I did fine the first day. Now I'm stuck. So be careful how you build the layout of the rooms. 

Oh, and if you want to start all over, the rooms reset. Let's see if you can take up this challenge. Find the mysterious 46th room. If you can get there, that is.

PROS:
- Simple story, unique gameplay (find the secret room);
- Good atmospheric music (doesn't bother the player);
- Puzzles, strategy, coins, fruits, keys, key cards (puts the mind at work);
- Common achievements + 11 hidden ones;
- Beautifully crafted rooms (as background images would be cool);
- Keeps you engaged to play and do your best.

NEUTER:
- I would recommend the developers to permanently put the layout on the left, so when the player has to select one of the three rooms to draft. I have to click the Tab every time to see how to draft the rooms.

CONS:
- When you click on a door, you cannot exit to rethink your strategy. Once you click a door, you have to draft a room no matter what;
- If you want to exit the game, it won't let you. The player will lose that day of exploration. There are two options: Save & Continue and Save & Quit. You cannot quit mid-exploring.

I haven't made it to the end yet. Where could that secret room be? Come on, friends. Let's split up. Maybe you're lucky and find it on the first try.
